# No emojis or decorative UI icons

The user does not want emojis or small decorative symbols in interfaces, buttons, labels, or chat-facing copy.

## Do not use

- Emoji in HTML/UI (e.g. chart, sparkle, file, checkmark emojis)
- Emoji as stand-in for icons in upload zones, CTAs, or step headers
- Decorative Unicode symbols meant to "prettify" the UI

## Use instead

- Plain Hebrew/English text only
- CSS for layout, color, borders, and emphasis
- Real image assets only when the user explicitly provides or requests them (e.g. GINI background)

## Examples

```html
<!-- BAD -->
<div class="zone-icon">📊</div>
<button>✨ הורד קובץ</button>

<!-- GOOD -->
<div class="zone-title">לחצו לבחירת קובץ אקסל או CSV</div>
<button>הורד Excel (.xlsx)</button>
```
